      • generateMemberID

        public java.lang.String generateMemberID()
        This method returns a unique ID. It generates a 6 digit random number followed by "919" using seed value 20L. Increment the _919_couner before returning the String. Examples:
        919649853
        919656567
        Returns:
        - String Unique member ID

      • addItems

        public void addItems(Item item)
              throws MaximumItemsReachedException,
                     UnderAgeException
        This method add items to items array. If itemsCount is less than length of the array then add items to array, else throw MaximumItemsReachedException with message "memberID : You have reached your maximum limit".

        If item is a Book,
        Check age of the member with age specified in Genre. If member's age is greater than or equal to age specified in Genre, then convert the book title to uppercase and update the book title, set the item available to false and then add the book to items array. Increment the itemsCount. Else, throw UnderAgeException with message "memberID : Not allowed to check out this book".

        If item is a DVD,
        Check age of the member with age specified in MPAA_Rating of DVD. If member's age is greater than age specified in MPAA_Rating, then convert the DVD title to lowercase and update the DVD title, set the item available to false and then add the DVD to items array. Increment the itemsCount. Else, throw UnderAgeException with message "memberID : The DVD has a MPAA_rating description rating, Your are not allowed to check out this item".

        If item is a device,
        Convert the device title to lower case and update the device title, set the item available to false and then add device to items array. Increment the itemsCount.
        Parameters:
        item - argument to the method
        Throws:
        MaximumItemsReachedException - if items array is full.
        UnderAgeException - if age of member is less than the specified age.
